## Some More NHST Interpretation Examples

1.  Is there a relationship between narcissism (DV = NPI) and testosterone?

```{r}
h <- read.csv("~/Dropbox/!WHY STATS/Class Datasets/hormone_data.csv", stringsAsFactors = T)
mod1 <- lm(NPI ~ test, data = h)
plot(NPI ~ test, data = h)
abline(mod1, lwd = 5)
summary(mod1)
```

1.  Is there a relationship between narcissism (DV = NPI) and sex?

```{r}
library(gplots)
mod2 <- lm(NPI ~ sex, data = h)
plotmeans(NPI ~ sex, data = h, connect = F)
summary(mod2)
```

1.  Is there a relationship between testosterone (DV = test) and sex?

```{r}
mod3 <- lm(test ~ sex, data = h)
plotmeans(test ~ sex, data = h, connect = F)
summary(mod3)
```
